      <body>
         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
                  <expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan>
                  <g type="hedera"/>            
                  <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan>.
               <lb n="2"/>
                  <persName>
                     <name type="gentilicium" key="Iulia">Iulia</name>
                     <name type="cognomen" key="Voluptas"><choice><corr>V</corr><sic>B</sic></choice>oluptas</name>                   
                  </persName>
                  <choice><corr>v</corr><sic>b</sic></choice>i
               <lb n="3" break="no"/>
                  xit annis
                  <num value="23">XXIII</num>
                  men
              <lb n="4" break="no"/>
                  sibus 
                  <num value="3">III</num>
                  diebus
                  <num value="24">XXIIII</num>;
               <lb n="5"/>
                  <persName>
                     <name type="gentilicium" key="Varia">Varia</name>
                     <name type="cognomen" key="Rodope">Rodope</name>                    
                  </persName>
                  alum
              <lb n="6" break="no"/>
                  nae bene merenti fecit.
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>
               To the divine spirits. Julia Voluptas lived for twenty-three years, three months, and twenty-four days;
               Varia Rodope made (this) for her well-deserving child.
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>
               Line 2: B for V is a common substitution. Thus, a reading of "Voluptas" makes more sense. Similarly, read "vixit."
            </p>
         </div>
